content:
Publish Articles and Translations

Publishing articles and translations makes them visible in all channels selected. If you publish an article that has translations, all translations of the article are published as well.

Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience

To publish, go to the Article Management tab or the article’s or translation’s detail page. You need the publish permission on an article's article type and the “Publish Articles” or “Publish Translated Articles” article action to publish.

You can choose to publish directly or schedule publishing for a future date and time. Publication times occur in 15-minute intervals, therefore we cannot guarantee publication will match the exact time you specify.

A scheduled article’s pending icon isn’t supported for list views. The Cancel Publication button isn’t available from a draft article in Lightning Experience.

If the draft being published is a working copy of a currently published article, it is published as a new version of the original. You can flag an already published article to make the new article icon display next to your article in selected channels.

Scheduling a publication removes any assignment information. Conflicts might occur when different agents perform actions on the same articles simultaneously.

Publishing Actions Available in Translated Articles:

* Assign: Draft Primary, Draft Translation
* Submit for Translation: Draft Primary, Published Primary
* Publish: Draft Primary, Draft Translation
* Archive: Published Primary
* Edit: Draft Primary, Draft Translation
* Edit as Draft: Published Primary
* Delete: Draft Primary, Draft Translation
* Change Record Type: Draft Primary
* Submit for Approval: Draft Primary
title: Publishing Articles and Translations in Salesforce
